The real doc- trine of Epicurus, upon this subject, appears to be as follows : In common with the philosophers of every school, he believed in the eternity of matter ; for they all equally conceived it an absurdity to suppose that the Deity himself could create any thing outv of no- thing: but that though matter existed from all eter- nity, there was a time when it was first endowed by the intelligent eternal Cause with powers of motion, and a consequent capability of organization and order.
